defaultContent determined to be illegal tends to fall under one of three categories, namely child abuse imagery, material intended to promote terrorism and content infringing copyright.
defaultChild abuse imagery
default3.4
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultSky is a member of t
defaulthe 
defaultInternet 
defaultWatch Foundation (“IWF “)
default, which 
defaultis 
defaultthe UK Hotline for reporting online child abuse imagery.  Its key role is to get content removed at source.  Where content is hosted in the UK, the IWF is typically able to get it removed in under an hour.   Where conten
defaultt is hosted overseas, it takes longer to get it removed.  However, the IWF
default provides its members with a list of URLs which contain illegal content.  Sky ensures that requests to access such webpages
default, regardless of where they are hosted, 
defaultresult in a ‘splashp
defaultage’ being served that informs the user that they 
defaultattempted
default to access a page that contains illegal content.  
